# Project rules for NutriLog

- Always preserve the MVP scope unless explicitly told to expand it.
- Prefer mobile-first UI decisions.
- Do not introduce authentication, cloud databases, or unnecessary infrastructure.
- Use shared schemas and types when practical.
- Keep components and services small and readable.
- Update root `agents.md` and `docs/` when major architectural/product decisions change.
- Before adding a new dependency, justify why it is needed.
- Prefer extensible interfaces over hardcoded vendor lock-in.
- AI food scan provider must remain swappable.
- Never store uploaded food images permanently.
- Persist only approved metadata for uploads.
- Suggestions must stay practical and non-medical.
- Weekly reporting must stay simple and readable.